        ${h3('Disciplines')}
        
        <p>Regular backgrounds are occupational, they represent the skills and everyday experience that one
        picks up in that background. They are not rolled for attacks or defence, even if they are military in
        nature, because that is not what they represent. If a player wants a character who has trained with a
        specific weapon or in a particular style then they should invest in a Discipline instead. These
        represent the time and dedication that the player has put into their martial training. As an example:-</p>
        
        <p><em>Thaddeus has the soldier background but all that represents is the regular training a soldier receives. He
        can march all day, run with a heavy pack, traverse any assault course you care to mention. He understands military
        commands and the rank structure. He can take care of his kit, strip and clean his assault rifle but it does not make
        him an exceptional marksman. To represent the additional training he took on, down at the firing range, whilst his
        buddies drank, and had lives, he needs to buy a discipline.</em></p>
        
        <p>Most of the Disciplines are specialised. Swordsman Longsword is a martial background that only applies
        when the bearer wields a longsword. If the bearer lost his longsword then he would not be able to use the
        background using another type of sword. For example:-</p>
        
        <p><em>Thaddeus has taken the discipline Marksman Assault Rifle because that is the weapon of choice in his
        armed force. When using an assault rifle he can use his background for attacks (but not defence it's a ranged
        weapon). During his first fire fight his rifle jams and he picks up a combat shotgun. He cannot use his background
        for this weapon, he hasn't trained enough with it, and so will just have to use his base POP.
        As a general rule melee martial backgrounds can be used with MEP and PAR and ranged disciplines can
        only used with POP. If the martial background works differently it will says so in the description.</em></p>
        
